description._content: Centennial Skating Palace, later known as Centennial Skating Rink, at Bondi Junction was used for roller skating, roller skating hockey, dances and public meetings. In 1913, it was advertised as 'THE LARGEST ROLLER RINK IN AUSTRALIA.. ROLLER SKATING ... Refreshing Recreation ... The Fashionable Winter Pastime at SYDNEY'S MOST POPULAR RINK...' Sydney Morning Herald 5 April 1913.
